ckv: Cayingon congtong dayli to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to yencominco
english: President Tsai Ing-wen's Apology to the Indigenous Peoples on Behalf of the Government.

ckv: ta ngayaw na ozosa betin yao ozosa tasawan na setangi, ta niomanan semangi to sasiqetan maw sampaw nangan zao, maken sinangan ti to yencomin. zao nangan, ossa wanma mai ti qeniyan azo mai temaytayta to lazat ay nangan zao, padames semano to "maken ay lazat na lawlaw" ta nani yencominco. maqezi taziyan taytan ta, tangi, padames pa ita pasa meRaqat ngayaw. azas pa iko to Raya na lawlaw ta, semano to yencominco meniz, maqezi ta teRe na anem niaq nisobatan zao. qeni masangan osepat Rasibo tasawan, qenataRaw na anem seRay temisin timaimoan ay lanas, aiko pa dayli to Raya na lawlaw ta, semobat timaimoan.
english: On this day 22 years ago, the term "shanbao" (mountain people) in the Additional Articles of our Constitution was replaced with the proper name: "indigenous people." This correction not only did away with a discriminatory term, but also highlighted the status of indigenous peoples as Taiwan's "original owners." From this basis, today, we are taking another step forward. To all indigenous peoples of Taiwan: On behalf of the government, I express to you our deepest apology. For the four centuries of pain and mistreatment you have endured, I apologize to you on behalf of the government.

ckv: sazemaken iko, temozos to tangi, ta kikinilan na qenabinnos ta, yao pama lazat semano to Raypa semobat zin na. nazao ya waway na, Raqana ta tangi deddanan pa zokat timaikoan mazas to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat. yao a zana masang mowaza temisin na azo mai to niana zin na ay, oo yao zana masang qenataRaw na anem na zoma lazatan, semano mazemon nani toRoz na qawman qanazao qenazapanan senaqay na lazat zin na, zao a miRi imi tangi taziyan, ngid imi oman seRay paliwaliw to kenasianem na waway zao.
english: I know that even now, there are some around us who see no need to apologize. But that is the most important reason why I am representing the government to issue this apology today. To see what was unfair in the past as a matter of course, or to treat the pain of other ethnic peoples as an unavoidable part of human development, this is the first mindset that we, standing here today, resolve to change and overturn.

ckv: qatatatian pa iko sikawma, semano to manna semobat iko to yencominco. ta melanayan na lawlaw zao, ezan ti ta ngayaw na osepat Rasibo tasawan yao ti lazat qemizowan. qemizowan taziyan ay lazat maw simonang qenabinos na, yao zana qaniyao ay sikawman na, wawaway na, pelisin na, sakialan na to saqabinosan saqaqanan na. timango, mai semolol qaniyao, yao ti zoma lazat mawto ta melanayan zao.
english: Let me put in simple terms why we are apologizing to the indigenous peoples. Four hundred years ago, there were already people living in Taiwan. These first inhabitants lived their lives and had their own languages, cultures, customs, and domains. But then, without their consent, another group of people arrived on these shores, and in the course of history, took everything from the first inhabitants who, on the land they have known most intimately, became displaced, foreign, non-mainstream, and marginalized.

ckv: siangato waway zao nani, ta toRoz mawto ay lazatan, miRaw to maw zana taziyan ay nianiana. ta qananaman na taziyan ay lazat mai ti to melanay, mai ti to qaizowanan, liwaliw ti azo ta zoman qaizowanan ay lazat mawto taziyan qemizowan, ossa ezano taziyan ay lazat qaniyao. maken ngid sinangan ossiq lazatan, paqiRi nani pasi maqezi ta qataRawan na anem na zoma ay lazatan. azo mai ta semano to aita nani ossiq maken mai temisin ay lawlaw, nayao qaninan pa ita temayta to wawaway na zao masang, sanoan ta pa niana makezaq ay, moman si niana qaninanan ay, Raya na lawlaw ta paqangi pa ita maken qasianem to zao zana masang ay lazas, zao a manna miRi ko tangi taziyan.
english: The success of one ethnic people can be built on the suffering of another. Unless we deny that we are a country of justice, we must face up to this history. We must tell the truth. And then, most importantly, the government must genuinely reflect on this past. This is why I stand here today.

ckv: yao ossiq sodad "taywan tongse". ta ngayaw ta monna ay nisodad na semano "taywan mai to waway na masang. Relan siangato, ti cengchengkong paqiRi, cingcaw meRibon." zao nani kenasianem na bosos. yencominco ezan ti ta ngayaw na otatani melalazan tasawan, yao ti ta melanayan zao, yao mowaza waway na seRay qenasanem na to melanayan zao, mai tomqez temozos to tangi. wanayka, aita wanma soppaR semano to pawRat miRaw zin ta semodad to zana masang, Raqana daily ko to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to yencominco.
english: There is a book called "The General History of Taiwan" published in 1920. In its foreword are these words: "Taiwan had no history. The Dutch pioneered it, the Koxinga Kingdom built it, and the Qing Empire managed it." This is a typical Han view of history. The truth is that indigenous peoples have been here for thousands of years, with rich culture and wisdom that have been passed down through generations. But we only know to write history from the perspective of the dominant. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ckv: Relan seRay ti cengcengkong meRibon nani metong to lazat seRay miRaw to Ribang, saqonga to banang, cingcaw ti meRibon nani padames meRaRaynang ti, mabobod pematezto lazat na yencomim, ta zipon ti meRibon nani qateteReq ti semano to naqoqonian, temozos molpon masawa to conghoamingkoo semangi ti to Ribonan to ta naongan ay, pasasetaRan na to ta dasidasan siakayan ay. qeni osepat Rasibo tasawan, omawto ta lawlawan ta ay, nizo masawa, mabobod, miRaw to melanay, qemabsi mesosozep to tongos na waway na saRibonan na yancominco. Raqana, dayli iko to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to yencominco.
english: The Dutch and the Koxinga Kingdom massacred and exploited the Pingpu ethnic group. The Qing Empire presided over bloody confrontations and suppression. Colonial Japan put in place comprehensive savage policies. And the post- war ROC government undertook assimilation policies. For 400 years, every regime that has come to Taiwan has brutally violated the rights of indigenous peoples through armed invasion and land seizure. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ckv: azoan na to waway na masang meRibon to damo na yencominco, yao zana masang ay qenasanem na maRames to zana tangi. wanayka, ta setangi ay senangi na Raya na lawlaw ta, Rayngo ti meRibon yencominco to tongos na waway na, lanas na, sapaqiRian na. wawaway na masang mai ti, mai ti sazemakenan na Raya na lawlaw ta to tongos na ay waway. Raqana dayli iko to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to yencomincoco.
english: Indigenous peoples maintain tribal order according to traditional customs, and ecological balance according to traditional wisdom. But in the process of modern state-building, indigenous peoples lost the right to steer their own course and govern their own affairs. The fabric of traditional societies was torn apart, and the collective rights of peoples were not recognized. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ckv: yencominco maw yao sikawman na, yao ti ya zipon qemabsi seRay sasetaRan na to waway na qaniyao paqiRi, yao qaya melaziw ti to 1945 tasaw, yao a Raya na lawlaw ta semano to sokaw sikawma to tongos na sikawman na baqibai na yencominco, Raqana qasiR mai ti tongos na sikawman na baqibai na yencominco. mowaza sikawman na pimpoco mai ti meniz. qeniyan ay Raya na lawlaw ta mai medames to Ribonan to masang ay waway na yencominco, taziyan, dayli ko to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to yencominco.
english: Indigenous peoples had their own languages. However, with Japanese rule aiming to assimilate and turn all into imperial subjects, and with the ROC government banning tribal languages after 1945, indigenous peoples' languages suffered great losses. Most Pingpu languages have disappeared. Successive governments have been negligent in the protection of indigenous cultures. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ckv: onnay tasaw, yao a Raya na lawlaw ta mai semano Rayngoan na lazat na yami, yao a sokaw to izip qasitaRaw to Rayngo paisingan ay dasamRosRos RosRos sepawan na ta lanyi. yao a lazat na lanyi en zin na to yao dasam ay RosRos qemabsi to izip na qaniyo. Raqana dayli ko to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to lazat na yami.
english: Without the knowledge of the Yami tribe, the government stored nuclear waste on Orchid Island. Tribe members on the island had to suffer the negative consequences. For this, I apologize to the Yami people on behalf of the government.

ckv: qeni yao ta zoman lawlaw ay lazat temoqaz to taywan, monna maqabsi ay nani qemizoan ta zaya ta dasidasan ay lazat na pimpoco. qeniyan miRaw ay lazat qonna na qemabsi ya lazat na pimpoco seRay nangan na, Raqana, yao iko qaya taziyan dayli to Raya na lawlaw ta semobat to pimpoco.
english: Ever since outsiders began arriving in Taiwan, the Pingpu ethnic group on the western plains have born the brunt of the impact. One ruling power after another eroded the individual and collective identities of the Pingpu ethnic group. For this, I apologize to the Pingpu ethnic group on behalf of the government.

ckv: ngid paliwaliw ti waway nani yao nisano na to Raya na lawlaw ta to niana qangidan na yencominco, sololan na Raya na lawlaw ta, malemes qaya semangi, tangi, yao nengi ay senangian to yencominco cipenfoa, wanayka, zao sasiqetan, mai meninan ya pakelawkawayan na Raya ta. mengasan semangi qaniyao, mai nizan na paqangi kasianem, mai nipaqangi meniz, lanas zao, dayli ko to Raya na lawlaw ta, semobat to yencominco.
english: After the democratic transition, the country began to respond to the appeals of indigenous movements. The government made certain promises and efforts. Today, we have an Indigenous Peoples Basic Law that is quite advanced. However, government agencies have not given sufficient weight to this law. Our actions have not been fast enough, comprehensive enough or sound enough. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ckv: taywan sinangan yao mowaza tatezoma naqoqoni ay wawaway, sikawman, Ribang, qaizoanan. wanayka, temozos to tangi ta yao a izip na, satodan na, niRaykelisiw na to saqayaoan na yencomincoan, yao ti ya congce melabo mowaza ti naqoqoni ay na, qawqawman Raya qenatanaq na. yao qaya, ta aneman na zanno yao mai temaytayta to yencominco, yao pama tangi. mai qasemin nisangi na pakelawkawayan na Raya na lawlaw ta, Raqana tangi sosozepan na pama zoma lazatan, yao a yencominco matazay to qataRawan na anem na, matazay to mesosozep qapilayan na anem na ay. nazao, dayli ko to Raya na lawlaw ta, semobat to yencominco.
english: Taiwan is known as a culturally diverse society. But even today, indicators on health, education, economic livelihood, political participation and more still show gaps between indigenous and non- indigenous peoples. Meanwhile, stereotypes and even discrimination against indigenous peoples have not gone away. The government has not done enough, so indigenous peoples have suffered pain and frustration unknown to other ethnic peoples. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ckv: mai qasemin ni padames niaq, yao qaya qeniyan, mai imi kalamaz temayta to mai kasemin qenalemes niaq, qawka yao ti tamaimoan taRaw na piliay na anem, temozos to tangi. maken melisaw ti imi. semobat imi, mengsan ti dames, wanayka zao Rosiangato pama. mai Raya anem ko osepat Rasibo ti tasawan qenapilay qenataRaw na anem nomi, ossiq ma sodad, ossiq ma sikawman qanengi ti anem nomi? wanayka, maken sazemaken anem ko, tangi semobat iko, siangatoan ta aita saleppawan lazat to simqanengian ta meniz.
english: Our efforts have fallen short, and succeeding generations have been blind to this inadequacy. Because of this, your hardship has continued to this day. For this we are truly sorry. Today's apology is long overdue, but it is a beginning. I do not expect any one speech or phrase of apology to wipe away four centuries of pain and suffering by the indigenous peoples. But I do hope with all my heart that today's apology will set this country and all its people on the path towards reconciliation.

ckv: sano pa iko to ossiq qenasanem na sikawman na yencominco, ta tangi taziyan. yao ta sikawman na tayal, semano to maken ay nani "balay "zin na. simqanengi zin na imi na nani "Sbalay " zao ya Balay ta ngayawan na toRangan na to "S." maken simqanengi zin na imi na sodad zao ozosa matapon. sikawman na ti to maken simqanengi, wanma patengayaw to maken ay lanas zao, pasi qawka maken sasetaR anem ta.
english: Please allow me to shed light on this occasion with a piece of indigenous wisdom. In the Atayal language, truth is called "Balay," and reconciliation is called "Sbalay," so you simply add an "S" sound to "Balay." Truth and reconciliation are in fact two related concepts. In other words, only by facing the truth sincerely can reconciliation be attained.

ckv: ta wawayan na yencominco, azo yao lazat mesosozep to ta damoan ay lazat, maken yao anem na ngid simqanengi, mesosozep to lazat ay qomRas to baRqian seRay nisosozep na ay lazat, palisinpo. malisinpo, ossa qatoRias semobat, sano pa qaniyao kinnawsa, to maqezi ta anem na maken ay kenasinem na naqoni aizipna. molepon semano to maken ay naqoni senaqay na qenazapan na qeniyan, paqanan na ti na baRqian to nansakopo Raq, melaziw ti ay, maken palaziwan ta. zao a "Sbalay" zin na.
english: In indigenous cultures, when a tribe member has offended another and intends to reconcile, an elder brings together the offender and the offended - not to produce a direct apology, but to allow each side to frankly share their inner journeys. When this truth-telling concludes, the elder calls for everyone to drink together, so that what is past is truly past. This is "Sbalay."

ckv: melana iko to tangi taziyan ta nazawan ay qaizoanan, yao a Raya na lawlaw ta seRay yencominco "Sbalay." melisaw na masang ay, maken zana masang ay, semano iko to maken maqezi ta aneman ko ay sikawman. antangi, yao paqenanem yencominco ay kapot ta sano pa to kenasianem na. mai ko kasianem papawRat to tangi sazemakenan timaikoan, wanayka, maken sazemaken ka melana timaikoan, qenalisaw na masang mai imi oman, ta lawlawan zao, qayao ossiq deddan, maken pasa simqanengi aita.
english: I hope today's occasion can be a "Sbalay" between the government and the indigenous peoples. I have spoken of past mistakes and truths the best I can, with nothing held back. In a moment, our indigenous friends will speak. I do not dare ask you to forgive, here and now. But I sincerely ask you to sustain the hope that past wrongs will not be repeated, and that one day, this country can see true reconciliation.

ckv: tangi Rosiangato pama, qazawan to qasimqanengian, ossa ta lazatan na yencominco seRay lazat na pimpoco, qawanay ya Raya na lawlaw ta qemazaw, soppaRan ko, wanma ta sikawman semobat mai qasemin, naqoni nipanmoan to yencominco, qawanay Raya na lawlaw maken naqoni senangi na maken pa simqanengi.
english: Today is only a beginning. The duty for reconciliation lies not with the indigenous peoples and the Pingpu ethnic group, but with the government. I know that words of apology alone are not enough. What we actually do for the indigenous peoples will decide whether reconciliation succeeds or stumbles.

ckv: tangi taziyan sano pa iko to mazemon, ta congtongfoan paqiRi pa to "maqezaq ay waway na yancominco seRay paliwaliwan to maqezaq ay weiyeanhoy." aiko pa sinangan to paazasan to lawlaw mazas, mazas to nipazoqat na tatezoma ay lazat na yancominco matapon kemilim to maqezaq ay waway na masang, yao qaya qasasetaR pa ya nangan ta qaRaya qaibabaw, qosazoi naqonian ta pa paqiRi ya lawlaw ta.
english: Therefore, I am here to announce that we are setting up an Indigenous Historical Justice and Transitional Justice Commission under the Presidential Office. As the head of state, I will serve as convener and work hand in hand with tribal representatives to pursue historical justice. We will also discuss, on the basis of equality, the future policy direction of this country.

ckv: padames pa iko semano, "congtongfoan weiyeanhoy", qaninanan nani Raya na lawlaw ta seRay yencominco sasetaR qaibabaw nangan na. pazokat ya yencominco to lazat na qalisimpoan simsano naqonian na pa pazokat, yao qaya pimpoco, minco seRay damo qanizo sasetaR anem na qawka, zao senangian qayao yencominco matapon simsano paqiRi, qawka maken pazokat to kenasianem na anem na lazat na damo.
english: I want to stress that this commission places the greatest importance on equality between the country and the indigenous peoples. The election of tribal representatives, including for the Pingpu ethnic group, will take as basis the consensus of peoples and tribes. This commission will serve as a mechanism for collective decision-making by indigenous peoples, and will ensure that the voices of tribe members find true expression.

ckv: yao qaya, sano pa iko to sincengyen pazokatan to deddan na pataz pa malisimpo simsano "semangi semozoq to sasiqetan." ta weiyeanhoyan sasetaR pa anem na paqiRi, qosazoi ay Raya na lawlaw ta, temozos to yen ay qaibabaw nangan na, manmo simsano semangi to nazao ay lanas. zao lanas qayao kemilim to zana masang ay, semozoq to yencominco pa meRibon to tongos na ay qaizowanan, sasetaR pa nipaqiRi na to daytanan ay, semozoq to satodan ay seRay wawaway na ay, qanengian to izip, yao qaya meRibon to qanengian na ta siyakayan ay...mowaza pama.
english: In addition, I will request that our Executive Yuan convene regularly the Indigenous Peoples Basic Law Promotion Committee, and use the Yuan's authority to coordinate and handle matters related to any consensus reached by the above-mentioned commission. These matters include the following: to retrieve historical memories, to promote indigenous self-government, to seek fair economic development, to ensure continuation of culture and education, to safeguard indigenous health, and to protect the rights of urban indigenous peoples, etc.

ckv: yao zana tangi ay sasiqetan seRay waway na zana masang, mai sasetaR ay, paqiRi pa ita to mezaki to waway ta "qaizowanan manmo to sasiqetan ta na yencominco," yao ti qinonongan to senangian to waway na yencominco masang seRay zana Raya na lawlaw ta tangi ay sasiqetan, mai pa padames simzoqoR sasiqetan.
english: Where modern laws and indigenous traditional cultures are at odds, we will set up an Indigenous Legal Service Center with a high degree of cultural sensitivity, to reduce through institutional design the growing clashes between indigenous customs and modern laws.

ckv: sano pa iko to pakelawkawayan na Raya to zao ay, qalazokan semangi, zana masang ay qenanaman na yancomin ay wawaway, ta qaizowanan na masang, ossa ngid simsedes oo baliw, azo zao yao semalaw to ossa saRibon ay pasan, semano to melisaw paqowadan oo mapolet ti. yao nazaw ay lanas, gingkiw pa ita to naqonia ita semangi.
english: I will ask the relevant agencies to immediately pull together cases in which indigenous community members have been indicted or sentenced for hunting, where the hunting was done in accordance with traditional customs, on traditional lands, and for non-transactional needs, and where the animals hunted were not protected by conservation laws. For such cases we will deliberate solutions.

ckv: sano pa iko to meRibon to "satowaq ay RosRos," sepawan na ta lanyi simsano to naqoni lanas zao, kinsan na pa pazokat semano to maken ya naqoni lanas zao. satowaq ay RosRos zao mai pama nipaqangi si, konna na pa bola to lazat na lanyi to kelisiw bonay to anem na qanengian to izip naqaniyao.
english: I will also direct relevant agencies to present an investigative report on the decision-making process of nuclear waste storage on Orchid Island. Before finding a permanent solution for the nuclear waste, we will provide the Yami tribe appropriate compensation.

ckv: yao qaya, moRebo iko to pimqoco ngid sinangan, sazemaken to tiana qaniyao, qazi pa imi ta ngayaw na osiwa bolan otolo betin deddan, simsano to sasiqetan, yao a pimqoco ay lazat qayao pa nangn na.
english: At the same time, under the principle of respecting the Pingpu ethnic group's self- identity, and recognizing their identity, we will examine relevant laws before September 30 of this year, so that Pingpu ethnic group identity will receive the rights and status it deserves.

ckv: tangi tasaw Rabetin yao ossiq bolan ossiq deddanan, siangato pa imi temolis, pazokat to mayni melanay na yencominco masang, semangi to qalisimpoan simsano ay lazat, siangato ti imi semozoq, qosazoi, qanengian na yencominco meRibon to tongos na ay Ribang melanay, qalolosiqan palopon. qalazokan niaq pa, yao a qaninanan na yencominco ay "sasiqetan to ngid Ribon yencominco to tongos na ay" "sasiqetan to melanay na seRay lazing na yencominco" "sasiqetan to paqeRaya semozoq to sikawman," tongawan na pa pasa lifoayen keminsa.
english: On November 1 of this year, we will begin to delineate and announce indigenous traditional territories and lands. The system of tribal public corporation is already in place. In the future, the ideals of indigenous self-government will be realized step by step. We will step up the pace and submit for legislative deliberation three laws of great importance to indigenous peoples: the Indigenous Peoples Self-Government Law, the Indigenous Peoples Land and Sea Areas Law, and the Indigenous Languages Development Law.

ckv: tangi qemadanan, temingaR ti imi to hoygian to pakelawkawyan na yencominco meniz. ta hoygian, sano pa Raya na lawlaw ta to mowaza padames to qanengian. qosazoi pitasaw ta owalo bolan ossiq deddanan, sano pa singcengyen to lazat na lawlaw ta meniz temozos ti taniyan nisangi na to maqezaq ay waway na masang seRay niliwaliw na to maqezaq ay. maken pa semangi to maqezaq ay waway na yencominco masang, yao qaya naqoni nipaqiRi na to yencominco pa meRibon to tongos na ay qaizowanan, zao otolo Raya ay sasangian na Raya na lawlaw to waway na yencominco.
english: Later this afternoon, we will convene a national indigenous peoples administrative meeting. In that meeting, the government will elaborate on the policies. On every August 1 to come, the Executive Yuan will report to the indigenous peoples our progress on restoring historical justice and transitional justice. To implement the Indigenous Peoples Basic Law, to serve indigenous historical justice, and to lay the foundation for indigenous self- government - these are the three major goals for the government's policy towards indigenous peoples.

ckv: tingaR pa iko to tangi taziyan ay seRay ta tilibian, ta owangloan pazoqat semano ay meniz yencominco ay kapot, masolon temayta meRibon. temingaR iko to qalaboaban meniz meRibon, ossa mawto pozin. temingR to lazat ta yencominco, kapot, padames ka meRibon, semano to naqoniyan, maken pa mezokat nisano na Raya na lawlaw ta, maken pa moman meliwaliw to melisaw na masang.
english: To all of our indigenous friends here and watching on TV and online: I invite you to stand witness. I invite you not to endorse, but to oversee. Please keep pressure on the government and right its course where necessary, so that it will realize its commitments and right historical wrongs.

ckv: wanay zin ko to meniz yencominco ay kapot, aimo semano to lazat na ta lawlaw zao, nitebeR na zapan ay melanay, seRay zana masang ay waway, qenaninanan na mai to Ribang qadayli. zao mesiRis qaninanan ay, bolay ta to qaReboan nangan.
english: I want to thank all of our indigenous friends. You remind everyone in this country that there is irreplaceable value in the land we tread on and the traditions we inherit. This value deserves dignity.

ckv: qosazoi ta nisozoqan ta semangi, yao pa baqbaqi na lazat na yencominco, seRay ta lawlawan, ta melanayan zao meniz lazat na yencominco, mai pa mai to soni, mai pa moman mai to qenasinengesan to masang ay, padanes mai pa maqamay wawaway na masang, mai pa mengangaw mai to maken ay qaizowan ta melanayan zao.
english: In the future, we will push for policies to ensure that succeeding generations of indigenous tribes and all ethnic peoples in Taiwan never lose their languages and memories, that they are never separated from their cultural traditions, and that never again are they lost in a land of their own.

ckv: tawik pa iko to meniz qeminowan taziyan ay lazat kasosolon pa ita malemes, qasoppaR pa ita to pazokat moman to waway ta masang, qasoppaR pa ita to melanay ta, qasoppaR pa ita to tatezoma ay wawaway na lazatan. pasa simqanengi pa ita semaqay, matapon qenabinosan seRay sasetaR sinangan, semaqay pasa taso ay qosazoi ay taywan.
english: I call upon our entire society to come together and get to know our history, get to know our land, and get to know the cultures of our many ethnic peoples. Let us work towards reconciliation, a shared existence and shared prosperity, and a new future for Taiwan.

ckv: tawik pa iko semano to meniz lazat na lawlaw ta, ta tangi deddanan yao ita meniz, qasosolon pa ita padames paqiRi to ossiq mai to temisin ay lawlaw, ossiq maken mowaza tatezoma sasetaR ay nangan na lazat na lawlaw.
english: I call upon all citizens to seize the opportunities offered by this day - to join together, work hard, and build a country of justice, a country of true diversity and equality.

ckv: yao taytaanko a a siasin tangi nani.
zaqis to paRin ta moloan qimolo.
english: climbed up the tree to pluck oranges.

ckv: yao osiq a tazongan siqayton nani simqaRiway.
english: There was a girl riding a bicycle and then collided with.

ckv: sokaw lazan msoRaw ti a sonis 'nay.
english: The road was uneven, the child fell.

ckv: to tmiboq ti a molo 'nay tamelanayan.
english: The oranges fell onto the ground.

ckv: tawian tangayaoanna nani yao a m kinspat a sonis a mawRat.
english: In the front there, there were four children playing around.

ckv: taytaanna to msoRaw qaqayton ay sonis to.

english: Not yet. haven't begun (barking the banana trees).

That child saw in the morning.

ckv: nani yao waso 'nay tatoRozanna na iza 'nay na siRemoq a yao.
english: The dog is behind something... the deer.

ckv: to yao ti ta wak wakianna tawakianna na siRemoq 'nay sonis 'nay.

ckv: nani masolon to wasona 'nay siRemoq a yao.

ckv: to Rayngoanna sayza to iza o to niano 'nay niwozonganko zinna sayza na siRemoq a yao nani.
english: did not know what it shouldered. It may think, 'What did I shoulder?'

ckv: moRetot ti ta izaan to maseq taqidisan to.

ckv: tmiboq ti ya sonis 'nay ato waso a yao.
english: The child and the dog fell down.

ckv: to wiya ti pasazi ti tayan ta iRoRan tazanzanoman a waso a zao ato sonis 'nay.

ckv: nani wozonganna ti pamoqoanna na sonis 'nay 'nay soni 'nay waso a yao.
english: The child carried that dog on the shoulders.

ckv: nani yao ti qalimka zinna to to waso a yao na sonis 'nay tayan ta paRinan 'nay.

ckv: to yao ti mzaqis ta babawan na paRin 'nay sonis 'nay ato waso.

nani titaanna yao a biat 'nay ozosa tawnayan.
english: They saw that there were two frogs there.

pasa libeng tmayta nani mwaza 'nay biat a yao talibeng na na paRin a yao.
english: looked downward and saw many frogs below the wood.

ckv: to taytaanna ti sayza na wiya ti qaniyao nani taytaanna ya biat a yao nani.
english: They left, looking at those frogs.

ckv: qawiya ti imi zinna to biat 'nay.
english: He said to the frogs, 'We are leaving!'

ckv: yao ti tababawan na na paRin a yao ya biat a yao mniz mazmon.

ckv: temengo maynep ti sonis ayto waso.

ckv: mRaRiw ti biyat 'nay nizi ta bodoqan.
english: The frog ran out of the bottle.
The child and that dog woke up.

ckv: nani kikiliman na sonis 'nay ayto waso 'nay biyat.

ckv: timengo pasosoRanna na waso 'nay oRona pasazi ta bodoqan nani.
english: And then that dog put his head into the bottle.

ckv: Rayngo ti ala 'nay oRona tabodoqan ma.
english: It couldn't pull its head out of the bottle.

ckv: nani bedonganna ti sonis'nay bodoq 'nay kawka ma ala oRona waso 'nay.
english: The bottle was broken by that child, and then the head of the dog was taken out.

ckv: nani matiw ti sa naong kmilim wi qmeRas to biyat 'nay sa naong.
english: They went to the mountain and kept searching, and they called to that frog in the mountain.

ckv: nani ma titaanna ti osiq 'nay eh osiq tangan tangan na na moton.

ckv: yao waso 'nay titaanna 'nay ta ta paRinan 'nay.

I forget how to say that.

ckv: nani mzaqis ti sonis 'nay pasazoi ta paRinan.

The frog was not there, either.

ckv: temengo tateRaq na paRin yao e adam.
english: And then, there was a bird inside the tree.

ckv: moRetot sonis 'nay tmiboq ti tapaRinan nizi tapaRinan sonis 'nay.

ckv: temengo e tanozanna penay 'nay waso 'nay wi tanozanna.
english: And then, the bees continued chasing the dog.

ckv: adam 'nay nani tanozan na sonis'nay qaya.
english: The bird continued chasing that child.
The child also climbed up to the rock.

ckv: temengo tatoRoz na beto yao 'nay sizi.
english: And then, there was a goat behind the rock.

ckv: qapaR zana sonis 'nay 'nay si waki na sizi 'nay.

ckv: tayan qmeRas to kmilim to biyatna nani.
english: He called and looked for his frog there.
He didn't know that the goat was there.
And then, the goat got up.
It threw him into the deep river.

ckv: 'nay iRoR ayto waso 'nay nizanna kinawsa baksiw.
english: It threw them, both the dog and the child.

ckv: nani mnangoy ti sonis 'nay ayto waso 'nay pasa qazqaz.

ckv: timengo ti ta na tatoRoz na paRin yao.
english: And then, at the back of the tree there were...

ckv: qalimetka qalimetka zin na sonis 'nay to waso 'nay.
english: The child said to the dog, 'Be quiet! Be quiet!'
Behind the tree, there was the frog.

ckv: e nanapaw kinawsa yao opito sonis na biyat 'nay.

ckv: nani titaanna 'nay nanapaw tam tinana tamana na biyat 'nay.

ckv: sonis zao ngid iko to qodo to osiq biyat zinna titaanna mlizaq to biyat nani.
english: 'I want to keep one frog,' thought the child. He saw and liked the frog.

ckv: bolaanna ti tamana tinana to osiq to sonis 'nay sapatanananso zinna.
english: The father and mother gave one frog to that child. 'One for you to bring home.'

ckv: nani wanay xiexieni wanay zin na tina na sonis 'nay to tama tamana tinana.
english: 'Thank you,' the child said to its father and mother.

ckv: yao sonis a yao tmayta to biyat 'nay ta tateRaqan na peRasko.
english: There was a child looking at the frog in the bottle.

ckv: Raytongozanna ti na waso a yao biyat biyat a yao ta teRaqan na peRasko.

ckv: maynep ti sonis a yao ato 'nay sizi 'nay.
english: The child and the goat fell sleep.

ckv: nani biyat a yao nayzi ta teRaq na peRasko nani mzokat ti.

ckv: biyat a yao izipna o mzokat ti.

ckv: ngid ti qa iza qazokat pasazi tapeRaskoan.

The child was sleeping. He didn't know.

ckv: nani masoat sonis a yao ato waso 'nay nani.

ckv: mai ti ya biyat a yao ta teRaq na peRasko.

ckv: pameng ti sonis 'nay masoat ngid sikozo.

ckv: nani yao ti qaysoRanna na a Raytongoz ti 'nay waso a yao ta izaan na na inpanna.

ckv: tangayawan na inpanna ya peRasko a yao mai ti to simpez.

ckv: izaanna ti na waso a yao peRasko 'nay niqazoanan na 'nay biyat isisanna ti na waso 'nay.

ckv: 'nay peRasko a yao mai ti to simpez.
english: There was nothing in the bottle.

ckv: mRaRiw ti ya biyat a yao.

ckv: yao ti ta tantanganan tmayta sonis a yao to biyat a yao sayza.

m yao ti alaanna ti na sonis a yao 'nay waso a yao.

ckv: tazian ti ya qmqeqeRas ti sonis 'nay to biyat a yao sayza.

ckv: ti Raytongozan na waso a zao ta bongoRan na paRin a yao.

ckv: nani yao sonis a zao tmayta to to biyat a yao tazian ta izaan o ta liapan na paRin.

yao ko a yao tababaw na paRin nani.

ckv: moRetot ti sonis a yao sozitang.

ckv: mqoling ti sonis 'nay nayzi ta babaw na paRin.

Why did his hand grab upwards?

The child climbed up onto the deer.

ckv: yao tababawna toRozna na siRmoq a yao 'nay sonis a yao.

ckv: na na iza 'nay o qonianna sikawma smani qaya.

ckv: nani yao Raytonoz a waso a yao to siRmoq a yao.

ckv: yao tababaw na oRona pamoqoanna na na siRmoq a yao ya sonis a yao tangi.

ckv: tmiboq ti 'nay sonis a yao nayzi taoRoanna na iza loqenaw a yao.

ckv: siRmoq a yao tmiboq ti a ni pamoqoanna na na siRmoq a yao to sonis a yao nani.

ckv: tmiboq ti wiya ti pasazi ta talibeng waso a yao qaya mqoling ti pasazi talibengan.

ckv: tmiboq pasazi ta melanayan 'nay sonis a yao ato waso a yao nani.

ckv: pameng ti yao tababawanna na tababaw na beto sayza 'nay siRmoq a zao.

ckv: mnangoy tazanzanoman a waso a zao stangi.

ckv: yao ti ta babaw na paRin tangi mzaqis qaniyao ta izaan o tababaw na paRin.

ckv: taytaanna yao a ozosa biyat a yao tazian ta kinilanna na paRin a yao Raya ay paRin.

ckv: yao pama tangi tazanzanoman tangi sonis a zao ato waso a zao.

They hadn't arrived at the shore.

ckv: yao mwaza biyat a yao ta babaw na paRin.

ckv: mzaqis 'nay biyat a zao mniz mazmon ka.

ckv: mango yao mlaziw ay ya mqaqayton nani.

ckv: wiya ti isisanna ya osiq qanas.

Rayngoan na lazat a yao na wi mzaqis kmyala to byabas a yao nani.

Finally, the two collided with each other.

ckv: m soRaw ti ya yao a.
mqi Roziq ay to byabas a yao to osiq qanas nani.

ckv: mRosal ti ya byabos a yao qaniyao Roziqanna na lazat a yao.

ckv: iwaliw ti mai to e qayton.
english: It turned out that there was no bike.

toRozna nani yao a izao ya lazat a yao smaRoR ti.

ckv: e? mana mai ti to simpez a osiq ka.
zinna saiza na lazat a yao nawiz babaw mqibyabas nani.
english: The person picking guavas up the tree was thinking.

e m qaqayton mala ta byabas a yao nani.
english: rode the bike and took the guavas.

zinna na lazat a yao nani.
naRin mai ti mtayta ya qenaalaanna to niqiRoziqna to byabas a yao.
english: didn't see him steal the guavas.

ckv: mai ti mtayta ya ya qanas a yao.

ckv: qalisinpoanna ti ta qibian 'nay 'nay ta 'nay byabas a yao nani.

They put (the guavas onto the bicycle) again.

alaan na kapotna bola to qobo 'nay kapotna 'nay msoRaw ay sonis a yao nani.

yao ti 'nay kintolo ay yao ti qman to byabas a yao.
english: There were three people who were eating guavas.

ckv: wiya ti pasazi ta tatiboR sayza smaqay 'nay kintolo ay sonis a yao nani.
english: The three children went towards the south.
Perhaps to their home. I don't know.

ckv: yao a kapot sikapot to waso.
yao a qenodona to biyat qaya.
sasazay sayza biyat a yao nani.
tmayta ta biyat a yao waso 'nay yao.
english: That dog looked at the frog.

ckv: timeng a toRos ti sayza sonis a yao nani.
waso yao na maynap ti qaya.
maynap ti qaya sonis a zao zinna nani.

ckv: wiya ti mRaRiw yao biyat a yao melisit ti nani.
o titaanna ti na waso yao sayza.
english: Probably the dog saw (the frog was gone).

ckv: inainaRana ti lazatna ya sonis a yao nani.
english: kept awaking his master, that child.

ckv: mai ti ya biyat a yao to.
yao ti mkikilim Ray waso yao to.

ckv: qadanna qadanna sozizitang ti a izaanna o.

yao pama bosaR ay seRay deddan poli ay.

ckv: nayao si, tod aka aiso naqonian ta semangi to nazao ay ozosa tikas.

ckv: o! nengi! qosazoi qayao pa ti qapaRan ko.

ckv: kowaya! nayao si ngid iko to ossiq tengen ay qodos.

english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

qawto ka temayta yo! baliw to qodos kobo nizo yao.

ckv: nengi iso, ngid iko Rasa to senapowaR seRay niRamazan to imos ay 'si.

ckv: niz ti mabaliw. yao pama ya sani ay yopin, ngid iso Rasa ni?

ckv: kowaya! bola iko qaossiq, moman si qawka iko Rasa to 'may.

ckv: kowa, panmoan ko pa iso sepez ta lobosan, olima betin nazao.

ckv: ta pasanoan zao nani, paqesoppaR aizipna timaiko manna sinangan aizipna to nangan zao, pasimqananam timaiko to pinileppaw na seRay damo na.
english: During the interview, he introduced to me the origin of his name and also introduced me to his family and tribe.

ckv: mipil iko timaizipana, "manna ngid iso oman to nangan, masang ay waway temoki to nangan, sokaw ni?
english: I asked him why he insisted on changing his name. Wasn't the old registration method sufficient?

ckv: semano ti angaw ateng, "izan ta zata ay qeloqot qawka maken ay nangan ta. nangan ko nani, yao waway na lazatan niaq, leppaw niaq, tongos niaq to lazatan, ngid qazemon pa Raqit ta patadikod to nangan na."
english: angaw ateng said, "The names written in indigenous languages are our true names. My name represents our ethnic group, our family, our identity. I hope more fellow tribespeople can reclaim their own names."

ckv: siRab masolon iko to bai ko matiw sa qizoanan baliw, temiyam baliw. mowaza niazasan na bai ko to nipaloman na to tened, meRamaz to qaqanan na yencomin paqan to semaqsaqay ay.
english: Yesterday, I went to the market with my grandmother to set up a stall. My grandmother brought a lot of vegetables that she grew herself and also prepared indigenous cuisine for everyone.

ckv: mazemon ay melizaq to tiyam na bai ko, mazemon meRasa to sidi' seRay kakolot, mazemon qaya temadam to niRamazan na.
english: Everyone loved my grandmother's stall. Many people bought the chilis and African eggplants, and many people came to taste the dishes she cooked.

ckv: nengi qanan niRamazan na to tosozan, senapowaR seRay nitim ay 'si na baboy na naong Ramesan to tani, paqawto to mazemon semaqsaqay ay bangsis na, niz ti mawto paylit melana ta tiyaman niaq.
english: The Sessile Alternanthera and sticky rice she cooked were delicious, as well as the braised pork with maqaw pepper and wild boar meat. The flavors attracted many customers, and everyone lined up at our stall.

ckv: yao meRamaz bai ko nani, yao iko qomRas paqawto to semaqsaqay ay. balodoq iko ta kinilan, "tened zao nizo nipaloman niaq, mai poiyo ay, qalazok ka qawto Rasa yo!"
english: While my grandmother was cooking, I was on the side attracting customers. I shouted, "The vegetables are self-grown, all-natural and organic! Come and buy now!"

ckv: kikiya ma maniz ti baliw Ribang niaq, semano bai ko, "yao nipanmoan so qawka."
english: Our goods sold out quickly, and my grandmother said, "It's all thanks to your help."

ckv: ta wawayan zao, mowaza nisinanam ko to qenasoppaRan to tened seRay qaqanan na yencomin, soppaRan ko ti pilay temiyam baliw to Ribang.
english: Through this event, I learned about indigenous plants and food and experienced the hard work of running a stall.

ckv: nitaytan ko to waway na bai ko melizaq to qaqanan na lazatan niaq, moRebo iko timaizipana.
english: Seeing my grandmother's passion for traditional food, I feel very proud and honored.
